# Real-Time DSP

- All processing in `BackroomsProcessor::process` must be allocation-free
- Use `juce::AudioProcessorValueTreeState` for parameters
- Use `juce::SmoothedValue` for modulated filter/reverb/comp targets
- Prepare `juce::dsp::*` processors in `prepareToPlay` with `ProcessSpec`
- Use `juce::ScopedNoDenormals` in `processBlock`

## Parameter semantics

| ID | UI label | Role |
|---|---|---|
| corner | Corner | Muffled ↔ clear macro |
| hall | Hall | Reverb room size |
| depth | Depth | Extra darkness + level loss |
| mix | Mix | Global dry/wet |

After DSP changes, run tests and rebuild before claiming done.
